  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Introduction: Data using ultrasonography to confirm correct position of the gastric tube is&#xD;
      heterogeneous in approach sites, combination exams, and methodology.&#xD;
&#xD;
      Aim: Find the best strategy to confirm gastric tube placement to avoid immediate&#xD;
      complication.&#xD;
&#xD;
      Method: A randomized controlled trial was initiated to compare ultrasonography and standard&#xD;
      routine method, using non-inferiority design. The study will be conducted in one medical ICU&#xD;
      with 18 beds at a medical center within 1 year. The primary outcome is the correct rate as&#xD;
      comparing with the chest radiography in each group. Total 190 patients is needed with&#xD;
      estimated 10% drop-out rate.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
